President Donald J. Trump and Vice President Mike Pence held a second meeting with the Cabinet and senior members of the Administration to discuss ongoing Federal support for Hurricane Harvey response and recovery. The President emphasized the importance of all departments and agencies fully committing to supporting the Governors of Texas and Louisiana and saving lives as the top priority. The focus will now shift to mass care, restoring power, providing life-sustaining necessities, and economic recovery. The President urged survivors to follow the instructions of their State and local officials. The President and Vice President expressed their thoughts and prayers for those affected and recognized the efforts of volunteer and faith-based organizations assisting fellow Americans.